channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Confessions of a 1980s flight attendant
item.description: Ann Hood, a best-selling author, has recounted her adventures working as cabin crew on TWA flights in the 1980s in a book detailing the highs and lows of life during the early jet age.

item.title: List of winners at the 2024 Tony Awards
item.description: Jeremy Strong won the Tony Award for best actor in a play for his work on the revival of “An Enemy of the People” and Daniel Radcliffe won a featured actor trophy for his revival of “Merrily We Roll Along.”

item.title: June 13, 2024 Israel-Hamas war
item.description: The US-backed Gaza ceasefire proposal doesn't meet Hamas' demands for an end to the war, a senior official has told CNN. Osama Hamdan also said that "no one has an idea" how many of the hostages held in the enclave are alive.

item.title: 6/16/2024: Agency in Crisis; The Godfather of AI; The Underboss
item.description: First, a look inside Aliceville: A women’s federal prison. Then, hear from Geoffrey Hinton on the promise, risks of AI. And, Steven Van Zandt: The 60 Minutes Interview.

item.title: Biden and Zelensky lay out new US support for Ukraine
item.description: US President Joe Biden and Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky signed a new security agreement Thursday as world leaders gathered for the G7 summit in Italy.

item.title: 2 killed, 14 injured in shooting at Juneteenth celebration; police seek suspect
item.description: Police in Round Rock, Texas, have asked for the public's help in locating a suspect in connection with a shooting during a Juneteenth celebration that left two dead.

item.title: 6/16: The Takeout: Steve Coll
item.description: Author and journalist Steve Coll talks about the complicated relationship between the U.S. government and Saddam Hussein, and how events in 1979 shaped future events like the Sept. 11 attacks and the Iraq war.

item.title: Supreme Court maintains access to abortion pill in unanimous decision
item.description: The Supreme Court has issued a decision on whether the US Food and Drug Administration overstepped its authority by expanding access to the abortion pill mifepristone.

item.description: President Biden attended a star-studded fundraiser in California over the weekend. Meanwhile, former president Trump held a rally in Detroit. Skyler Henry reports.

item.title: Trump in Washington for meetings with Republican allies
item.description: Former President Donald Trump is back in Washington for the first time since becoming the presumptive Republican nominee as well as a convicted felon. Follow here for the latest live news updates.

item.title: 2 killed after World War II-era plane crashes near California airport: Officials
item.description: Two people were killed Saturday when the World War II historical plane crashed shortly after takeoff from Chino Airport, firefighters said.
